---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Insights" activeNav="insights">

  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="page-header-inner">
      <span class="section-label">Thinking &amp; Perspectives</span>
      <h1>Insights for Leaders</h1>
      <p>
        Frameworks, observations, and hard-won lessons from the intersection of
        strategy, leadership, and organizational change.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- FILTER BUTTONS -->
  <section class="filter-section">
    <div class="filter-inner">
      <div class="filter-bar">
        <button class="filter-btn active" data-filter="all">All</button>
        <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="strategy">Strategy</button>
        <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="leadership">Leadership</button>
        <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="teams">Teams</button>
        <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="execution">Execution</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FEATURED ARTICLE -->
  <section class="featured-article">
    <div class="featured-inner">
      <div class="featured-tag">
        <span class="eyebrow">Featured</span>
      </div>
      <div class="featured-content">
        <div class="featured-text">
          <span class="article-category">Strategy</span>
          <h2>The Three Questions Every Leadership Team Avoids &mdash; and Why They&rsquo;re the Most Important</h2>
          <p>
            In nearly every facilitated session I run, there are questions the room
            dances around. Not because they&rsquo;re sensitive &mdash; but because answering
            them honestly would force a decision. Here&rsquo;s how to name them, ask them,
            and actually get to the truth.
          </p>
          <div class="article-meta">
            <span class="meta-date">April 12, 2026</span>
            <span class="meta-divider">&middot;</span>
            <span class="meta-read">8 min read</span>
          </div>
          <a href="#" class="btn-white">Read the Article &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <div class="featured-visual">
          <div class="featured-number">01</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ARTICLES GRID -->
  <section class="articles-section">
    <div class="articles-inner">
      <div class="articles-grid">

        <article class="article-card">
          <div class="article-img-placeholder" data-category="Leadership"></div>
          <div class="article-body">
            <span class="article-category">Leadership</span>
            <h3>Why &ldquo;Strategic Clarity&rdquo; Is a Leadership Skill, Not a Planning Exercise</h3>
            <p>
              Most executives conflate clarity with agreement. They&rsquo;re not the same &mdash;
              and confusing the two is a major source of organizational drag.
            </p>
            <div class="article-meta">
              <span class="meta-date">March 28, 2026</span>
              <span class="meta-divider">&middot;</span>
              <span class="meta-read">6 min read</span>
            </div>
            <a href="#" class="article-link">Read more &rarr;</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="article-card">
          <div class="article-img-placeholder" data-category="Teams"></div>
          <div class="article-body">
            <span class="article-category">Teams</span>
            <h3>The Alignment Illusion: When Leadership Teams Think They Agree but Don&rsquo;t</h3>
            <p>
              Surface-level consensus is one of the most common and costly dynamics in
              high-performing organizations. Here&rsquo;s how to tell if your team has it.
            </p>
            <div class="article-meta">
              <span class="meta-date">March 14, 2026</span>
              <span class="meta-divider">&middot;</span>
              <span class="meta-read">5 min read</span>
            </div>
            <a href="#" class="article-link">Read more &rarr;</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="article-card">
          <div class="article-img-placeholder" data-category="Execution"></div>
          <div class="article-body">
            <span class="article-category">Execution</span>
            <h3>Deciding at Speed: A Framework for Executive Decisions Under Pressure</h3>
            <p>
              When the stakes are high and time is short, most leaders revert to the
              way they&rsquo;ve always decided. There&rsquo;s a better approach.
            </p>
            <div class="article-meta">
              <span class="meta-date">February 21, 2026</span>
              <span class="meta-divider">&middot;</span>
              <span class="meta-read">7 min read</span>
            </div>
            <a href="#" class="article-link">Read more &rarr;</a>
          </div>
        </article>

      </div>

      <div class="coming-soon-note">
        <span class="eyebrow">More Coming Soon</span>
        <p>New essays and frameworks are published monthly. Subscribe to get them directly.</p>
        <form class="subscribe-form" name="subscribe" method="POST">
          <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="your@email.com" required />
          <button type="submit" class="btn-teal">Subscribe</button>
        </form>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="cta-band">
    <div class="cta-band-inner">
      <span class="section-label">Work Together</span>
      <h2>Want These Frameworks Applied to Your Situation?</h2>
      <p>
        Reading is useful. Working through it with your team is transformative.
        Let&rsquo;s take the next step.
      </p>
      <div class="btn-group">
        <a href="/work-with-me" class="btn-white">Book a Session</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-ghost">Get in Touch</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</Layout>

<style>
  .filter-section {
    background: var(--white);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(30,58,95,0.07);
  }

  .filter-inner {
    max-width: 1140px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 48px;
  }

  .filter-bar {
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 24px 0;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .filter-btn {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--gray-mid);
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid rgba(30,58,95,0.12);
    border-radius: 100px;
    padding: 7px 18px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .filter-btn:hover {
    border-color: var(--teal);
    color: var(--teal);
  }

  .filter-btn.active {
    background: var(--navy);
    border-color: var(--navy);
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .featured-article {
    background: var(--navy);
    padding: 80px 0;
  }

  .featured-inner {
    max-width: 1140px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 48px;
  }

  .featured-tag {
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .featured-content {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 220px;
    gap: 64px;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .featured-text .article-category {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal-light);
    background: rgba(58,159,159,0.12);
    border: 1px solid rgba(58,159,159,0.25);
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 100px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .featured-text h2 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .featured-text > p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .article-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  .meta-divider {
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  .featured-visual {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .featured-number {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 8rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    line-height: 1;
    user-select: none;
  }

  .articles-section {
    padding: 80px 0;
    background: var(--off-white);
  }

  .articles-inner {
    max-width: 1140px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 48px;
  }

  .articles-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 28px;
    margin-bottom: 72px;
  }

  .article-card {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid rgba(30,58,95,0.07);
    border-radius: 16px;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
  }

  .article-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 16px 48px rgba(30,58,95,0.1);
  }

  .article-img-placeholder {
    height: 180px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--navy) 0%, #2a4a6f 100%);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .article-img-placeholder::after {
    content: attr(data-category);
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 16px;
    left: 20px;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4);
  }

  .article-body {
    padding: 28px 28px 32px;
  }

  .article-category {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .article-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--navy);
    line-height: 1.35;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .article-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--gray-dark);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .article-card .article-meta {
    color: var(--gray-mid);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .article-link {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--teal);
    text-decoration: none;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .article-link:hover {
    color: var(--teal-light);
  }

  .coming-soon-note {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 480px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .coming-soon-note .eyebrow {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .coming-soon-note p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--gray-mid);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  .subscribe-form {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    max-width: 400px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .subscribe-form input {
    flex: 1;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text);
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid rgba(30,58,95,0.12);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 11px 16px;
    outline: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .subscribe-form input:focus {
    border-color: var(--teal);
  }

  .subscribe-form .btn-teal {
    padding: 11px 24px;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    white-space: nowrap;
    border: none;
  }
</style>
